STEP 2 — FEATURE ENGINEERING

Create FeatureEngineer class:

Compute:

Global frequency vector

Rolling frequency (configurable window)

Gap score per number

50x50 co-occurrence matrix

Structural historical distributions:

sum

odd count

range spread

Return structured FeatureSet dataclass.

STEP 3 — BAYESIAN PROBABILITY ENGINE

Implement BayesianModel class:

Use Dirichlet prior alpha=1.

Compute posterior:

alpha_i' = alpha + freq_i

Probability:

P(i) = alpha_i' / sum(alpha')

Create composite probability:

Score_i =
w1 * P_bayes

w2 * P_roll

w3 * P_gap

Normalize final probabilities.

Return:

final_main_probabilities (size 50)

final_star_probabilities (size 12)

STEP 4 — MONTE CARLO ENGINE

MonteCarloSimulator class:

weighted_sample_without_replacement()

simulate_draw()

run_simulation(n_simulations: int, parallel=True)

Simulation must:

Generate synthetic draws

Compute structural metrics

Build percentile ranges for:

sum

odd count

spread

Return StructuralBounds dataclass:
sum_min, sum_max
allowed_odd_counts
spread_min, spread_max

Use multiprocessing for performance.

STEP 5 — RULE ENGINE

RuleEngine class:

Implement:

is_valid(ticket, structural_bounds)

Rules:

Sum within bounds

Odd count in allowed set

Max 2 consecutive numbers

No 4 numbers in same decade

No full repeat of last draw

Return boolean.

STEP 6 — TICKET SCORING

Implement TicketScorer:

Compute:

Log probability:
sum(log(P(number)))

Structural score:
1 - normalized distance from historical mean sum

Pair rarity score:
inverse of co-occurrence sum

Final fitness:

fitness =
lambda1 * log_prob

lambda2 * structural_score

lambda3 * pair_rarity

STEP 7 — GENETIC OPTIMIZER

GeneticOptimizer class:

initialize_population(n)

evaluate_population()

select_top(percent)

crossover(parent1, parent2)

mutate(ticket)

evolve(generations)

Constraints:

All offspring must pass RuleEngine

Avoid duplicate tickets

Penalize overlap between tickets

Population size configurable.

STEP 8 — FINAL TICKET POOL

TicketPoolGenerator class:

Pipeline:

Generate initial candidates via Monte Carlo sampling

Filter using RuleEngine

Run GeneticOptimizer

Remove high-overlap tickets

Ensure number coverage diversity

Return final N tickets

Each ticket should include:

numbers

stars

log_probability

structural_score

fitness

